All pairwise cross-sectional correlations at days 0, 10, and 30 between Feno values, prebronchodilation FEV0.5 values, and symptoms were weak and nonsignificant (see Fig E1 in this article's Online Repository at www.jacionline.org). However, when assessed longitudinally from day 0 to day 30, prebronchodilation FEV0.5 and Feno values were significantly associated both with each other and with symptoms (Fig 3
and Table III, Table IV
).
